
[1]sententious

   SENTEN'TIOUS, a.

   1. Abounding with sentences, axioms and maxims; short and energetic; as
   a sententious style or discourse; sententious truth.

   How he apes his sire,

   Ambitiously sententious. Addison.

   2. Comprising sentences; as sententious marks.

   [This should be sentential.]
